snippet.textDisplay: I had gone through a very difficult 9 months. The most painful tragic months of my life. I felt lost, helpless and hopeless. God in His knowledge had stripped me of everything and I in my complete human weakness had no-one and nowhere to turn to. At the high point of my struggle to survive, this song was released! Listening to it and reading the words gave me so much strength. I am stronger and ready to start living again. Thank you Kaavish & QB for being part of my struggle. We dont know each other but in the world of souls we met through this song and you lifted me up!

snippet.textDisplay:
With all due respect to one of my favorites, QB.... Jaffer Zaidi took this song to a whole new level with his soulful singing, brilliant music and heartfelt lyrics... This piece of brilliance totally belongs to him... With the way he began singing the first line, I knew this song would remain with me forever and ever... there's something truly magical about how this song has been picturized as well (being at the right moment at the right time) that makes watching this video a divine experience... 😌😌

Hope this doesn't remain underrated forever and reaches to its true potential...
